T1  - A result on the sign of restricted least-squares estimates
AU  - Leamer, Edward E.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 3
IS  - 4
SP  - 387
EP  - 390
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/11/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(75)90055-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440767590055X
AB  - When a variable is dropped from a least-squares regression equation, there can be no change in sign of any coefficient that is more significant than the coefficient of the omitted variable. More generally, a constrained least squares estimate of a parameter βj must lie in the interval (β̂j−V12jj|t|, β̂j + V12jj|t|) where β̂j is the unconstrained estimate of βj, V12jj is the standard error of β̂j and t is the t-value for testing the (univariate) restriction.
